translated: Lundgren, Sten Thore, provincial doctor in Jämjöslätt, born on January 6th, 1907 in Sigtuna, to parents Oscar L. and Karin Victoria Pettersson. Married in 1939 to nurse Stina-Brita Levin. Completed secondary school in Södertälje in 1926, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine in Stockholm in 1932, and a medical degree there in 1938. Temporary assistant doctor at Östhammar hospital in 1938, appointed doctor there the same year. Assistant doctor at Årjäng hospital from 1940-1942, assisting doctor at Umeå hospital in the medical department for five months in 1942. Assistant doctor at Garphyttan sanatorium from 1942-1943, temporary second doctor at Marieberg hospital in 1944, and served as a substitute doctor at various hospitals and sanatoriums as well as appointed as a provisional doctor after being a trainee doctor in Jämjöslätt district in 1946. Appointed as a provisional doctor in Kågedalen district since 1946.
